{
  "texts": [
    "It is important that published construct definitions are simultaneously human-and machine-readable.",
    "This imperative is included in the UNESCO Open Science recommendation (UNESCO, 2021) and put into practice in a rapidly growing number of recent innovations (Lakens & DeBruine, 2021; Metz et al., 2022; West, 2021).",
    "In order to achieve this machine-readability, a data serialization file format needs to be chosen, and we have chosen YAML (a recursive acronym that stands for \"YAML Ain't Markup Language\").",
    "This format is designed to be simultaneously human-readable and machine-readable.",
    "An additional advantage is that YAML is also a superset of the JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) standard, which means that DCTs can also be specified in JSON if researchers prefer (but note that YAML is more human-readable)."
  ]
}